What is the use of CASE in an UPDATE statement?

Answer:
CASE allows you to update different rows with different values in a single UPDATE statement based on multiple conditions, 
making updates more efficient and reducing the need for multiple queries.

SET SQL_SAFE_UPDATES = 0;

UPDATE Employee
SET salary = CASE
    WHEN dept_id = 101 THEN salary + 1000
    WHEN dept_id = 102 THEN salary + 1000
    WHEN dept_id = 103 THEN salary + 1000
    ELSE salary
END;


UPDATE Employee
SET salary = CASE
    WHEN dept_id = 101 THEN salary + 5000
    WHEN dept_id = 102 THEN salary + 3000
    WHEN dept_id = 103 THEN salary + 2000
    ELSE salary
END
WHERE dept_id IN (101, 102, 103);

